HEADWORD: Antevert
<hw>An`te*vert"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>antevertere</ets>; <ets>ante</ets> + <ets>vertere</ets> to
turn.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To prevent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>To displace by
anteversion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

